01:01.965 --> 01:03.232
Oh my God,
that was so gross.

01:03.300 --> 01:04.265
I had to hold my breath

01:04.333 --> 01:06.067
the entire time
I was in there.

01:06.135 --> 01:07.101
Max, move.

01:07.169 --> 01:08.469
Can you give me
that pacifier?

01:08.537 --> 01:10.471
Mm-hm.
Sorry.

01:10.539 --> 01:11.772
I'll put him in the back.

01:11.841 --> 01:15.143
You know what? Forget it.
We gotta get going!

01:15.211 --> 01:17.145
<i>Honey, we have to hurry</i>

01:17.213 --> 01:18.880
so we can get home
before they do.

01:18.948 --> 01:20.447
What, am I driving
a getaway car?

01:20.514 --> 01:22.582
No, I just wanna
make a good impression.

01:22.650 --> 01:24.117
You made a good
impression already, honey.

01:24.185 --> 01:25.252
God. Look at me.

01:25.320 --> 01:26.586
I am so gonna have
to change.

01:26.654 --> 01:27.420
Honey, you
don't have to change.

01:27.488 --> 01:28.922
You look fine.

01:28.990 --> 01:29.923
<i>Maybe to you,
but to your mom?</i>

01:31.226 --> 01:32.692
Lou, I told you.
They're not like that, okay?

01:32.760 --> 01:33.861
And if you didn't want them
to come in the first place...

01:33.928 --> 01:35.295
Yeah.
Not invite your parents

01:35.363 --> 01:38.297
to their granddaughter's
baby naming ceremony?

01:38.365 --> 01:39.365
Can you hand me
that cell phone?

01:39.432 --> 01:41.267
I have to give everyone
our ETA.

01:41.335 --> 01:42.468
Oh... shoot!

01:43.370 --> 01:45.037
Max... sorry.

01:46.106 --> 01:49.242
Oh, yeah, dog drool.
Least of my worries.

02:01.820 --> 02:02.921
Yeah!

02:10.127 --> 02:11.695
What a good boy!

02:11.763 --> 02:13.931
He seemed to handle
that distance really well.

02:13.999 --> 02:16.233
You know, he'd ride all day
if I let him.

02:16.301 --> 02:17.534
So what do you say,

02:17.602 --> 02:18.335
should we try him out
of the gate a few times?

02:18.403 --> 02:19.870
Yeah, it's about time.

02:19.938 --> 02:21.872
Just as long as you give him
a couple of days off.

02:21.940 --> 02:23.107
All right?
He needs to recover.

02:23.174 --> 02:24.374
Right, right.
'Cause you know the saying?

02:24.441 --> 02:25.474
Slow and steady...

02:25.542 --> 02:27.676
Comes in dead last.

02:27.744 --> 02:30.246
He's a race horse, Tim.

02:31.348 --> 02:33.249
Who needs a day off...

02:33.317 --> 02:34.750
<i>'Cause he deserves it.</i>

02:36.787 --> 02:37.987
Well, I gotta run.

02:38.055 --> 02:38.988
Do you mind cooling him out
for me?

02:39.056 --> 02:40.355
Yeah. Sure, honey.
Thanks.

02:40.423 --> 02:41.323
<i>I'll see you later tonight.</i>

02:41.391 --> 02:42.391
<i>Okay, honey.</i>

02:42.458 --> 02:44.859
Lou's coming home today.

02:44.928 --> 02:46.028
Great.

02:46.095 --> 02:49.064
Give her a big hug
for me.

02:49.132 --> 02:51.366
That was Lou.
They'll be here soon.

02:51.434 --> 02:53.835
Did you know that
the you-know-who's are coming?

02:53.903 --> 02:55.270
Last minute thing.

02:55.338 --> 02:56.770
How'd she sound?

02:56.838 --> 02:59.540
She sounds like she could use
a week at the spa.

02:59.607 --> 03:01.608
And this Bartlett
naming ceremony

03:01.676 --> 03:03.911
seems to be giving her
just a little bit of stress.

03:03.979 --> 03:06.314
Not sure why.
Couldn't be much simpler.

03:06.381 --> 03:10.051
My great grandfather
built this fireplace

03:10.118 --> 03:13.119
using stone he found
right here on Heartland.

03:13.187 --> 03:14.754
And when there's
a new arrival,

03:14.822 --> 03:17.090
well, the fire gets lit

03:17.158 --> 03:19.259
and we give him
or her a name

03:19.327 --> 03:21.761
and a stone to go with it.

03:21.829 --> 03:23.396
That sounds lovely.

03:23.464 --> 03:25.698
Where's your stone?

03:25.766 --> 03:27.300
<i>This one right here.</i>

03:27.368 --> 03:29.268
<i>Uh-oh! Loose!</i>

03:30.203 --> 03:32.972
Oh, nothing a little mortar
won't fix.

03:33.039 --> 03:34.406
And while I'm at it...

03:34.474 --> 03:37.042
You know, I can't quite
remember the last time

03:37.110 --> 03:40.446
I had a good look
up inside here.

03:40.513 --> 03:42.247
<i>Oh...</i>

03:42.315 --> 03:44.449
Boy, that is filthy.

03:44.516 --> 03:46.517
But we're gonna call
a professional, right?

03:48.653 --> 03:49.887
What was I thinking?

03:54.793 --> 03:56.060
Lou!

03:56.128 --> 03:57.528
Lou! Peter! Hey!

03:58.763 --> 04:00.663
Amy, shhh!

04:00.731 --> 04:03.033
She fussed all the way
across Saskatchewan.

04:03.101 --> 04:04.368
And trust me,

04:04.435 --> 04:07.037
that drive could put
anyone into a coma.

04:07.105 --> 04:08.438
Lou! Good to see you!

04:10.574 --> 04:12.042
Sorry.

04:12.110 --> 04:13.343
Nevermind.

04:13.411 --> 04:15.778
Nobody ever died
from a lack of sleep.

04:15.846 --> 04:16.812
I should know.

04:16.880 --> 04:17.779
Can I hold her?
Can I take her?

04:17.846 --> 04:18.981
No, Mallory.

04:19.048 --> 04:20.382
She's cranky
when she wakes up.

04:20.450 --> 04:21.884
She's cranky?

04:21.951 --> 04:24.353
Listen.
The baby barfed on my jeans.

04:24.421 --> 04:25.821
I've just spent a month
with a woman

04:25.889 --> 04:27.789
who makes me feel like
the world's worst mother,

04:27.857 --> 04:29.325
and I don't even wanna know

04:29.393 --> 04:31.427
what this stain
on my shirt is.

04:31.495 --> 04:33.061
<i>Here they come!</i>

04:33.129 --> 04:34.095
<i>Hey! Quiet you.</i>

04:41.770 --> 04:43.671
<i>Archie! Grace!</i>

04:44.606 --> 04:45.606
Welcome to Heartland!

04:51.579 --> 04:53.179
♪

04:54.179 --> 04:58.454
Heartland S05E03 - <font color="#FF8C00">What's in a name?</font>
Original airdate: October 2, 2011

